## Summary
Implements client-side sorting for the queue page with 5 sort options, persistent preferences, and comprehensive E2E test coverage.

Fixes #323

## Changes
- Added client-side sorting with 5 options: Queue Order, Title (A-Z), Title (Z-A), Recently Added, Format
- Sort preference persists in localStorage across page reloads
- Optimized performance with useMemo to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Shows actual queue positions (not display positions) to avoid confusion
- Comprehensive E2E test coverage with reliable waits

## Testing
- [x] All E2E tests pass (9/9 queue sort tests)
- [x] All backend tests pass (514/514)
- [x] Linting passes (make lint)
- [x] Type checking passes (ty check)
- [x] Manual testing completed

## Code Review Notes
**Initial Review Findings**:
- ✅ Fixed: Added useMemo to prevent re-sorting on every render (Critical)
- ✅ Fixed: Optimized date parsing to avoid redundant parsing (Critical)
- ✅ Fixed: Show actual queue position instead of display position (High)
- ✅ Fixed: Replaced magic timeouts with waitForLoadState (High)

**Performance Improvements**:
- Sorting now only runs when `threads` or `sortOption` changes
- Date parsing happens once per thread instead of O(n log n) times
- No performance degradation with large thread lists

**UX Improvements**:
- Queue positions always show actual database position
- Users won't be confused about display order vs queue order

## Screenshots
Sort dropdown in queue header (desktop and mobile)

